    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nIn https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/eef2aedff6313d85b852463c78614ace57bb6f56 or later with tmux and [lualine.nvim](https://github.com/nvim-lualine/lualine.nvim), the startup intro message is gone in a flash. This issue doesn't appear outside tmux or inside tmux without `window-{,active-}style`.\r\n\r\ntmux version: 3.4\r\nlualine version: https://github.com/nvim-lualine/lualine.nvim/commit/7d131a8d3ba5016229e8a1d08bf8782acea98852\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. `tmux -f minimal.conf`\r\n2. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\r\n\r\n`minimal.conf`\r\n```\r\nsetw -g window-style bg='#393939'\r\nsetw -g window-active-style bg='#2d2d2d'\r\n```\r\n\r\n`minimal.lua`\r\n```lua\r\nlocal tmpdir = vim.uv.os_tmpdir()\r\nlocal plugin_dir = vim.fs.joinpath(tmpdir, 'nvim_intro_is_gone')\r\n\r\nif not vim.uv.fs_stat(plugin_dir) then\r\n  vim.fn.system({\r\n    'git',\r\n    'clone',\r\n    'https://github.com/nvim-lualine/lualine.nvim',\r\n    plugin_dir,\r\n  })\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.opt.runtimepath:append(plugin_dir)\r\n\r\nrequire('lualine').setup()\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe startup intro message should still be displayed.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2440+g8addd2750\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux on WSL\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty 0.13.1 (fe2a3c56)\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ntmux-256color (xterm-256color outside tmux)\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
